# Astro Portfolio – Project Conventions

## Stack
- **Astro v5** with static output (`output: "static"`)
- **Tailwind CSS v3** via `@astrojs/tailwind` (base styles disabled — use `src/styles/global.css`)
- **MDX** integration is installed; current content collections use plain **Markdown**
- **TypeScript** for logic by default; `src/pages/rss.xml.js` is an intentional exception in the current codebase

## Design Tokens (Tailwind)
Use custom tokens instead of arbitrary values:

| Token | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| `ink` | Page background |
| `mist` | Body copy / secondary text |
| `cloud` | Primary accent (links, labels) |
| `aurora` | Success / availability badge |
| `steel` | Metadata / dates |
| `line` | Border color |
| `panel` | Card background |
| `glow` | Box shadow on cards |
| `grid` | Background grid pattern |

## Utility Classes (global.css)
Prefer these semantic classes over repeating Tailwind chains:
- `shell` — card/panel with border + shadow
- `section-title` — eyebrow label
- `section-heading` — large section heading
- `button-primary` / `button-secondary` — CTA buttons
- `copy-muted` — muted paragraph text
- `prose-cloud` — rich text styling for content pages
- `panel-card` / `tag-chip` / `terminal-*` — recurring UI patterns already defined in the project

## Site Metadata
All site-level constants live in `src/lib/site.ts`. Import from there — never hardcode name, URL, social links, or OG image metadata.

## Content Collections
Collections are defined in `src/content.config.ts`. Always use `getCollection()` to fetch entries. Never read markdown files manually.

## Build And Deploy
- `npm run build` is the acceptance gate; it generates `public/og-image.png` and then runs `astro build`
- Static output is written to `dist/`
- Cloudflare Worker config lives in `wrangler.jsonc` and serves `./dist`
- GitHub Actions validation should focus on install, build, Wrangler dry-run, and generated output
